src: The film centers on a reclusive wealthy family who has spent months living in virtual isolation in the family mansion to prevent their community from finding out that daughter Hélène has gotten pregnant from a one-night stand, only to have their fragile equilibrium challenged when Hélène abandons the house soon after the baby's birth to look for the father.

mt: The film follows an isolated wealthy family. || In order to stop their community from knowing that the daughter Hélène is pregnant after a one-night stand, they do not leave their mansion for months. || When Hélène gives birth and runs away from the home to look for the father, the fragile balance of the home breaks.

src: In southwestern Ontario, Highway 401 was closed for much of December 23 between London and Tilbury, west of Chatham, due to about 100 vehicles, including numerous tractor trailers, being involved in multiple collisions, while Highway 402 was closed between London and Sarnia because of a 50-vehicle pileup and deteriorating conditions.
mt: In southwestern Ontario, due to deteriorating conditions and multiple collisions, Highway 401 was shut down between London and Tilbury, near Chatham, on December 23. || Additionally, a 50-vehicle pileup caused the closure of Highway 402 between London and Sarnia.

src: In southwestern Ontario, Highway 401 was closed for much of December 23 between London and Tilbury, west of Chatham, due to about 100 vehicles, including numerous tractor trailers, being involved in multiple collisions, while Highway 402 was closed between London and Sarnia because of a 50-vehicle pileup and deteriorating conditions.
